---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Taylor Series for e^x — Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Watch polynomial approximations converge to e^x — add terms and see how quickly the Maclaurin series locks onto the curve."
>
  <section class="demo-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Taylor Series for e^x</h1>

      <div class="explanation">
        <p>I found this in my math homework and had to look it up because it seemed wrong. The claim is that e^x — which is this irrational, transcendental number that goes on forever — can be approximated by a regular polynomial.</p>
        <p>A polynomial is just: a + bx + cx² + dx³... Normal stuff. But the Maclaurin series says if you pick the coefficients just right (1, 1, 1/2, 1/6, 1/24...), your polynomial tracks e^x almost perfectly near x=0. Add more terms and the range where it works keeps growing.</p>
        <p>The slider starts at degree 1 (just a straight line). By degree 5, you can barely see the gap near x=0. Watch the error graph at the bottom — the area shrinks as you add terms.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-container">
        <h2>Polynomial Approximation</h2>
        <canvas id="mainCanvas" role="img" aria-label="Graph showing e^x and its Taylor polynomial approximations at different degrees"></canvas>

        <div class="controls">
          <div class="control-group">
            <label for="degreeSlider">
              Polynomial Degree: <span id="degreeLabel">N</span> = <span id="degreeValue">1</span>
            </label>
            <input type="range" id="degreeSlider" min="1" max="5" step="1" value="1">
          </div>

          <div class="button-group">
            <button id="addTermBtn">Add Next Term</button>
            <button id="resetBtn">Reset</button>
            <button id="showAllBtn">Show All Terms</button>
          </div>

          <div class="stats">
            <div class="formula" id="formulaDisplay">P<sub>1</sub>(x) = 1 + x</div>
            <div class="error-readout">
              <span>Error at x=1: |e<sup>1</sup> - P<sub id="errDegree1">1</sub>(1)| = <span id="errorAt1" class="error-val">0.000000</span></span>
              <span>Error at x=2: |e<sup>2</sup> - P<sub id="errDegree2">1</sub>(2)| = <span id="errorAt2" class="error-val">0.000000</span></span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h3>Absolute Error |e^x - P<sub id="errorDegreeLabel">1</sub>(x)|</h3>
        <canvas id="errorCanvas" role="img" aria-label="Graph showing the absolute error between e^x and the current Taylor polynomial approximation"></canvas>
      </div>

      <div class="why-matters">
        <h2>Why Calculators Can Actually Compute e^x</h2>
        <p>Your calculator can't compute e^x directly — transcendental functions don't have exact finite representations. So what does it actually do? It uses a polynomial approximation like this. With enough terms, the error is smaller than the display precision, so it looks exact.</p>
        <p>The coefficients (1, 1, 1/2, 1/6, 1/24, 1/120...) are 1/n! — they come from the derivatives of e^x, which are all also e^x. That self-referential property is what makes e^x special and why this particular series converges so cleanly.</p>
        <p>Physics simulations, signal processing, financial models — anything involving exponential growth or decay is computing an approximation like this underneath. The degree slider you're moving literally controls how accurate the computation would be.</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="demo-nav">
        <a href="/math-explorations/geometric-series">← Geometric Series</a>
        <a href="/math-explorations">Back to Math Explorations →</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .demo-page {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  h3 {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }

  .explanation {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--purple);
  }

  .explanation p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .demo-container {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  canvas {
    width: 100%;
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    display: block;
  }

  #mainCanvas {
    height: 280px;
  }

  #errorCanvas {
    height: 140px;
  }

  .controls {
    margin: var(--space-lg) 0;
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
  }

  .control-group {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  label {
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  #degreeValue {
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #E74C3C;
  }

  input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--mid-gray);
    outline: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--purple);
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--purple);
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
  }

  .button-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  button {
    width: 100%;
    min-height: 44px;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .button-group {
      flex-direction: row;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    button {
      width: auto;
      min-width: 120px;
    }
  }

  .stats {
    background-color: var(--white);
    border-radius: 4px;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
  }

  .formula {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-size: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
    color: var(--charcoal);
    overflow-wrap: break-word;
  }

  .error-readout {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  .error-val {
    font-family: 'Courier New', monospace;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--purple);
  }

  .why-matters {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-2xl) auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--orange);
  }

  .why-matters p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .demo-nav {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .demo-nav a {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    * { animation: none !important; transition: none !important; }
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    #mainCanvas {
      height: 400px;
    }

    #errorCanvas {
      height: 180px;
    }

    .error-readout {
      flex-direction: row;
      gap: var(--space-lg);
    }

    .formula {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }

    .demo-nav {
      flex-direction: row;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const mainCanvas = document.getElementById('mainCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const errorCanvas = document.getElementById('errorCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const degreeSlider = document.getElementById('degreeSlider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const degreeValue = document.getElementById('degreeValue') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const formulaDisplay = document.getElementById('formulaDisplay') as HTMLDivElement;
  const errorAt1 = document.getElementById('errorAt1') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const errorAt2 = document.getElementById('errorAt2') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const errDegree1 = document.getElementById('errDegree1') as HTMLElement;
  const errDegree2 = document.getElementById('errDegree2') as HTMLElement;
  const errorDegreeLabel = document.getElementById('errorDegreeLabel') as HTMLElement;
  const addTermBtn = document.getElementById('addTermBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const showAllBtn = document.getElementById('showAllBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;

  // Degree color map
  const degreeColors: Record<number, string> = {
    1: '#E74C3C',
    2: '#E67E22',
    3: '#27AE60',
    4: '#3498DB',
    5: '#9B59B6',
  };

  // Formula strings (using subscript-compatible HTML)
  const formulaHTML: Record<number, string> = {
    1: 'P<sub>1</sub>(x) = 1 + x',
    2: 'P<sub>2</sub>(x) = 1 + x + x\u00B2/2',
    3: 'P<sub>3</sub>(x) = 1 + x + x\u00B2/2 + x\u00B3/6',
    4: 'P<sub>4</sub>(x) = 1 + x + x\u00B2/2 + x\u00B3/6 + x\u2074/24',
    5: 'P<sub>5</sub>(x) = 1 + x + x\u00B2/2 + x\u00B3/6 + x\u2074/24 + x\u2075/120',
  };

  function setupCanvas(canvas: HTMLCanvasElement): { ctx: CanvasRenderingContext2D; width: number; height: number } {
    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
    const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    canvas.width = rect.width * dpr;
    canvas.height = rect.height * dpr;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
    return { ctx, width: rect.width, height: rect.height };
  }

  function factorial(n: number): number {
    if (n <= 1) return 1;
    let result = 1;
    for (let i = 2; i <= n; i++) result *= i;
    return result;
  }

  function evalPoly(x: number, degree: number): number {
    let sum = 0;
    for (let n = 0; n <= degree; n++) {
      sum += Math.pow(x, n) / factorial(n);
    }
    return sum;
  }

  // Coordinate transform helpers for main canvas
  // x-axis: -3 to 3, y-axis: -3 to 20
  const X_MIN = -3;
  const X_MAX = 3;
  const Y_MIN = -3;
  const Y_MAX = 20;

  function toPixelX(x: number, width: number): number {
    return ((x - X_MIN) / (X_MAX - X_MIN)) * width;
  }

  function toPixelY(y: number, height: number): number {
    return height - ((y - Y_MIN) / (Y_MAX - Y_MIN)) * height;
  }

  function drawMainCanvas(degree: number) {
    const { ctx, width, height } = setupCanvas(mainCanvas);

    // Clear
    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

    // Grid lines (very faint, every 1 unit in x and y)
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.05)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;

    for (let gx = Math.ceil(X_MIN); gx <= Math.floor(X_MAX); gx++) {
      const px = toPixelX(gx, width);
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(px, 0);
      ctx.lineTo(px, height);
      ctx.stroke();
    }
    for (let gy = Math.ceil(Y_MIN); gy <= Math.floor(Y_MAX); gy++) {
      const py = toPixelY(gy, height);
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(0, py);
      ctx.lineTo(width, py);
      ctx.stroke();
    }

    // Axes
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.25)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;

    // x-axis (y=0)
    const py0 = toPixelY(0, height);
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(0, py0);
    ctx.lineTo(width, py0);
    ctx.stroke();

    // y-axis (x=0)
    const px0 = toPixelX(0, width);
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(px0, 0);
    ctx.lineTo(px0, height);
    ctx.stroke();

    // Axis tick labels
    ctx.fillStyle = '#888888';
    ctx.font = '13px DM Sans';
    ctx.textAlign = 'center';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'top';
    for (let gx = X_MIN; gx <= X_MAX; gx++) {
      if (gx === 0) continue;
      const px = toPixelX(gx, width);
      ctx.fillText(String(gx), px, py0 + 4);
    }

    ctx.textAlign = 'right';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'middle';
    const yTickVals = [Y_MIN, 0, 5, 10, 15, Y_MAX];
    for (const gy of yTickVals) {
      const py = toPixelY(gy, height);
      ctx.fillText(String(gy), px0 - 4, py);
    }

    const SAMPLES = 500;

    // Draw previous degree approximation curves (faded)
    for (let d = 1; d < degree; d++) {
      const color = degreeColors[d];
      ctx.strokeStyle = color;
      ctx.globalAlpha = 0.4;
      ctx.lineWidth = 2;
      ctx.beginPath();
      let started = false;
      for (let i = 0; i <= SAMPLES; i++) {
        const x = X_MIN + (i / SAMPLES) * (X_MAX - X_MIN);
        const y = evalPoly(x, d);
        const px = toPixelX(x, width);
        const py = toPixelY(y, height);
        if (!started) {
          ctx.moveTo(px, Math.max(0, Math.min(height, py)));
          started = true;
        } else {
          ctx.lineTo(px, Math.max(0, Math.min(height, py)));
        }
      }
      ctx.stroke();
    }
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;

    // Draw current degree approximation (full color, 3px)
    const currentColor = degreeColors[degree];
    ctx.strokeStyle = currentColor;
    ctx.lineWidth = 3;
    ctx.beginPath();
    let polyStarted = false;
    for (let i = 0; i <= SAMPLES; i++) {
      const x = X_MIN + (i / SAMPLES) * (X_MAX - X_MIN);
      const y = evalPoly(x, degree);
      const px = toPixelX(x, width);
      const py = toPixelY(y, height);
      if (!polyStarted) {
        ctx.moveTo(px, Math.max(0, Math.min(height, py)));
        polyStarted = true;
      } else {
        ctx.lineTo(px, Math.max(0, Math.min(height, py)));
      }
    }
    ctx.stroke();

    // Draw true e^x — thick black dashed
    ctx.strokeStyle = '#000000';
    ctx.lineWidth = 3;
    ctx.setLineDash([6, 3]);
    ctx.beginPath();
    let expStarted = false;
    for (let i = 0; i <= SAMPLES; i++) {
      const x = X_MIN + (i / SAMPLES) * (X_MAX - X_MIN);
      const y = Math.exp(x);
      const px = toPixelX(x, width);
      const py = toPixelY(y, height);
      if (!expStarted) {
        ctx.moveTo(px, Math.max(0, Math.min(height, py)));
        expStarted = true;
      } else {
        ctx.lineTo(px, Math.max(0, Math.min(height, py)));
      }
    }
    ctx.stroke();
    ctx.setLineDash([]);

    // Legend: e^x label near top-right
    ctx.fillStyle = '#000000';
    ctx.font = '13px DM Sans';
    ctx.textAlign = 'right';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'top';
    ctx.fillText('— e^x (exact)', width - 8, 8);
  }

  function drawErrorCanvas(degree: number) {
    const { ctx, width, height } = setupCanvas(errorCanvas);

    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

    const ERR_Y_MAX = 5;
    const SAMPLES = 500;

    // Grid lines (faint)
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.05)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    for (let gx = Math.ceil(X_MIN); gx <= Math.floor(X_MAX); gx++) {
      const px = toPixelX(gx, width);
      ctx.beginPath();
      ctx.moveTo(px, 0);
      ctx.lineTo(px, height);
      ctx.stroke();
    }

    // Axes
    ctx.strokeStyle = 'rgba(0,0,0,0.25)';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
    // x-axis at bottom
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(0, height);
    ctx.lineTo(width, height);
    ctx.stroke();
    // y-axis
    const epx0 = toPixelX(0, width);
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(epx0, 0);
    ctx.lineTo(epx0, height);
    ctx.stroke();

    // Tick labels on x-axis
    ctx.fillStyle = '#888888';
    ctx.font = '13px DM Sans';
    ctx.textAlign = 'center';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'bottom';
    for (let gx = X_MIN; gx <= X_MAX; gx++) {
      if (gx === 0) continue;
      const px = toPixelX(gx, width);
      ctx.fillText(String(gx), px, height - 2);
    }

    const color = degreeColors[degree];

    // Compute error points
    const points: { px: number; py: number }[] = [];
    for (let i = 0; i <= SAMPLES; i++) {
      const x = X_MIN + (i / SAMPLES) * (X_MAX - X_MIN);
      const err = Math.abs(Math.exp(x) - evalPoly(x, degree));
      const clampedErr = Math.min(err, ERR_Y_MAX);
      const px = toPixelX(x, width);
      const py = height - (clampedErr / ERR_Y_MAX) * height;
      points.push({ px, py });
    }

    // Fill area under error curve
    ctx.fillStyle = color;
    ctx.globalAlpha = 0.2;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(points[0].px, height);
    for (const pt of points) {
      ctx.lineTo(pt.px, pt.py);
    }
    ctx.lineTo(points[points.length - 1].px, height);
    ctx.closePath();
    ctx.fill();
    ctx.globalAlpha = 1;

    // Draw error curve
    ctx.strokeStyle = color;
    ctx.lineWidth = 2;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(points[0].px, points[0].py);
    for (let i = 1; i < points.length; i++) {
      ctx.lineTo(points[i].px, points[i].py);
    }
    ctx.stroke();

    // Label top-left
    ctx.fillStyle = '#555555';
    ctx.font = '13px DM Sans';
    ctx.textAlign = 'left';
    ctx.textBaseline = 'top';
    ctx.fillText('Absolute Error |e\u02E3 \u2212 P\u2099(x)|', 6, 6);
  }

  function updateStats(degree: number) {
    const color = degreeColors[degree];

    // Update degree display color
    const degreeValueEl = degreeValue as HTMLSpanElement;
    degreeValueEl.textContent = String(degree);
    degreeValueEl.style.color = color;

    // Update formula
    formulaDisplay.innerHTML = formulaHTML[degree];

    // Update error labels
    errDegree1.textContent = String(degree);
    errDegree2.textContent = String(degree);
    errorDegreeLabel.textContent = String(degree);

    // Compute errors
    const e1 = Math.abs(Math.exp(1) - evalPoly(1, degree));
    const e2 = Math.abs(Math.exp(2) - evalPoly(2, degree));
    errorAt1.textContent = e1.toFixed(6);
    errorAt2.textContent = e2.toFixed(6);
    errorAt1.style.color = color;
    errorAt2.style.color = color;
  }

  function fullRedraw() {
    const degree = parseInt(degreeSlider.value, 10);
    drawMainCanvas(degree);
    drawErrorCanvas(degree);
    updateStats(degree);
  }

  degreeSlider.addEventListener('input', fullRedraw);

  addTermBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const current = parseInt(degreeSlider.value, 10);
    if (current < 5) {
      degreeSlider.value = String(current + 1);
      fullRedraw();
    }
  });

  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    degreeSlider.value = '1';
    fullRedraw();
  });

  showAllBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    degreeSlider.value = '5';
    fullRedraw();
  });

  const handleResize = () => { fullRedraw(); };
  window.addEventListener('resize', handleResize);
  document.addEventListener('astro:before-swap', () => {
    window.removeEventListener('resize', handleResize);
  });

  // Initial draw
  fullRedraw();
</script>
